   <titleInfo>
      <title>[Letter] 1828 May 20, Pleasant Plains [to] Miss Ann J[ane] Bell, Charlotte, Dickson County, Tennessee / Ann T Barry</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This document is a letter, dated May 20, 1828, to Ann Jane Bell in Dickson County, TN from her friend Ann T. Barry in Pleasant Ridge, TN. In the letter, Barry discusses her recent travels across the state, paying special attention to the landscape of the various counties and the variation in taste and color of their streams. She also expresses great awe at traversing the Tennessee River, and she discusses other news of family and friends, including the high rate of sickness and death in the region.</abstract>
